            What Is the 18 Month Sleep Regression?
          </h2>
          <p>
            The 18 month sleep regression is a temporary period when a toddler who previously slept well suddenly starts struggling with sleep. Despite the name, it doesn't happen on an exact schedule â€” some toddlers experience it as early as 15 or 16 months, while others don't hit it until closer to 20 months.
          </p>
          <p>
