            How Long Does the 18 Month Sleep Regression Last?
          </h2>
          <p>
            This is the question every exhausted parent asks first, and the honest answer is: <strong>typically 2 to 6 weeks</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            However, the actual duration depends heavily on two factors: what's driving the regression and how you respond to it. If the primary cause is teething, sleep will likely bounce back once the teeth break through. If it's more behavioural â€” boundary testing and habit changes â€” it can stretch longer if new sleep associations are accidentally created.
          </p>
          <p>
