            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 className="font-bold text-brand-charcoal mb-2">Why is my 18 month old suddenly waking at night?</h3>
              <p>
                At 18 months, multiple developmental factors converge: separation anxiety peaks, language development surges, independence-seeking begins, and teething pain from molars and canines disrupts comfort. Together, these can turn a previously great sleeper into a frequent waker.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 className="font-bold text-brand-charcoal mb-2">Should I drop to one nap during the 18 month regression?</h3>
